04/07/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- German Foreign Minister Frank-Walter Steinmeier called on BiH politicians to take on responsibility and ensure the realisation of crucial reforms, during a visit to Sarajevo on Monday (3 July). 
He met there with High Representative Christian Schwarz-Schilling, the BiH presidency members and others. 
While reaffirming support for BiH's EU bid, Steinmeier stressed the need to reform the police and the constitution after the 1 October general elections. 
The deadline passed on Monday for parties to submit their lists of candidates to the Central Election Commission. 
(Nezavisne novine, Dnevni avaz - 04/07/06; PBS BiH, RTRS - 03/07/06)
